    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of real estate, is a trust account where funds are held until certain conditions are met, such as the completion of construction or the transfer of ownership. It's a common practice in Canada, especially in Toronto, where escrow accounts can be set up for various purposes, like property taxes, insurance, and maintenance costs. You'll typically need to deposit funds into the escrow account before closing, which will be released once the conditions are met or canceled if they're not fulfilled. Think of it like a temporary holding cell for your money, ensuring that you're not paying for anything until the deal is finalized.",
      "source": "target",
